The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Citi buys 19.9% of Anand Rathis firm 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, March 23: Citigroup Venture Capital International (CVCI) is picking up a 19.9 per cent stake in Anand Rathi Securities for an undisclosed sum.

 CVCI is a leading foreign private equity investor. The funds raised from this stake purchase will be deployed for both organic and inorganic growth and for working capital requirements, Anand Rathi Securities announced today. 

 Sources close to the company said it has outlined a plan to expand in the country. 

 Anand Rathi Securities was set up in 1994 by Anand Rathi, the former president of Bombay Stock Exchange. It offers a variety of services that include wealth management, investment banking, brokerage and distribution of equities, commodities, mutual funds and insurance. 

 Chairman Anand Rathi said, We are happy to have CVCI as a financial partner with us for our long-term growth. Financial partnership with a renowned international fund like CVCI and extra resources will assist us in achieving faster growth. The funding will be used to expand the companys network of branches and create greater value for our customers through advanced technology. 

 The investment by CVCI is latest in the series of foreign companies taking keen interest in the countrys brokerages. 




